{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34b2fb47-289e-4e3d-8886-b334e606944c","content":"Great news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was the .NET 9 opt-in flag and is now unnecessary.\n\nYou can simplify your project file:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NWpv564HRNroYkcj5Yf34G","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f6afe479baaf4b69afd735fa7b56bb49/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f6afe479baaf4b69afd735fa7b56bb49/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"3b4a6da8-8997-40b8-ad67-37c2e0449002","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and asking about Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) support in `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner — the VSTest-based runner is no longer the default. This means:\n\n1. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is **no longer needed** — it was a .NET 9 opt-in property to enable the MTP integration with `dotnet test`. In .NET 10, this is the default behavior.\n\n\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required to configure the project as an executable test host using MTP.\n\nSo the user can safely remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` since .NET 10 SDK enables MTP-based `dotnet test` by default.","outputTokens":467,"requestId":"1BC7:1AB7E8:202D605:23980B3:6A03CF19"},"id":"a6dc1b59-abb3-4731-81d2-e58518c10fe1","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:08:49.615Z","parentId":"3f415d40-5940-4add-ac73-b5164bb24b03"}
