{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a9a4ea5-f5af-43bd-8c2f-0173c80af20a","content":"**Summary:**\n\n- **Remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — .NET 10's `dotnet test` natively speaks the MTP protocol; no opt-in needed.\n- **Keep `EnableMSTestRunner`** — this is still required to build your test project as an MTP executable host.\n- **Keep `OutputType` as `Exe`** — required by the MTP runner.\n\nYour updated `.csproj` now looks like:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual — it will use MTP automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3b4a6da8-8997-40b8-ad67-37c2e0449002","outputTokens":194,"requestId":"1BC9:361109:22254D1:2588E09:6A03CF21"},"id":"af415e4a-27ce-40a8-b923-70ca44a3fc88","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:08:55.066Z","parentId":"bd695c43-2e09-457a-9dcb-4ecb858f0b8c"}
